headline: G.O.P. in California Finds Its Old Swagger In Impeachment Fight
abstract: California leaders on both sides are playing an outsized role in Washington’s impeachment drama, reflecting the complex political landscape in the deep blue state.
lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — When The Sacramento Bee published a scathing editorial about the impeachment trial last week — using words like “deliberately misled” “betrayed” and “lied” — much of the newspaper’s wrath was directed not at President Trump, but at one of his leading defenders: Devin Nunes, a Republican congressman who represents the Central Valley.
keywords: Trump-Ukraine Whistle-blower Complaint and Impeachment Inquiry
